   "source": [
    "## Exploratory Data Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "#### This analysis explores how audio features of songs relate to their popularity. The goal is to identify which characteristics (e.g., danceability, energy, loudness) are most associated with higher popularity and to understand whether these relationships are linear or more complex.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### These insights will guide the use of a Random Forest Regressor to predict song popularity.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### We begin by analyzing the target variable, \"song_popularity\", to understand its distribution. This helps determine how predictable popularity may be and whether extreme values are common."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "b6ede206",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
